Place steak slices, onions and peppers in nonmetal dish. Add combined steak sauce and curry powder; stir to evenly coat steak and vegetables. Cover. Refrigerate 1 hour to marinate, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, soak skewers in water for at least 30 minutes. Preheat grill to medium-high heat. Drain steak slices and vegetables; discard marinade. Alternately thread steak (accordion style), vegetables and pineapple onto skewers. Grill kabobs 8 to 10 minutes or until cooked through, turning occasionally. Serve with the rice.